<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <!-- F024: the SECOND Phase-5 pure core ŌĆö the typed ship-decision vocabulary and the single pure,
       total `Ship.rollup : RouteResult -> RunMode -> Profile -> ShipDecision` that rolls an
       already-routed change (the F019 `RouteResult`) plus a chosen run MODE and PROFILE up into one
       whole-change SHIP DECISION: a closed `Pass`/`Fail` verdict, the deterministic
       `Blockers`/`Warnings`/`Passing` partition of every enforced item, each item's full F023
       enforcement detail, and a typed `ExitCodeBasis` (clean vs blocked) ŌĆö the design's
       "Modes, profiles, and maturity" rollup at change scale.

       It REUSES F023 `deriveEffectiveSeverity` for every per-item decision (FR-003) and the F019
       `RouteResult` / F018 `Gate` / F017 finding values VERBATIM (the "reuse, don't re-derive" rule).
       It adds only the whole-change rollup: the hidden gate/finding -> `EnforcementInput` mapping
       (FR-013, research D3/D4), a three-way `Blockers`/`Warnings`/`Passing` partition of every
       enforced item, and the verdict + exit-code-basis derived from that partition. It honours the
       design's no-hide rule ŌĆö a relaxed blocker is always visible as a self-explaining warning,
       every item carrying base + effective severity, mode, profile, maturity, and reason.

       PURE and TOTAL (FR-008): defined over the COMPLETE cross-product of (selected-gate maturities ├Ś
       finding zones ├Ś run mode ├Ś profile) ŌĆö INCLUDING the empty `RouteResult` (ŌćÆ `Pass`, empty lists,
       `Clean`) ŌĆö never throws, deterministic ŌĆö byte-identical for identical input (FR-009, SC-004).
       Echoes base severity unchanged (FR-006), drops no item (|B|+|W|+|P| = N+M, FR-010), never
       escalates a base-advisory item (FR-011).

       Computes NO `audit.json` (or other) serialized document, NO process exit code (only the typed
       `ExitCodeBasis`), NO cache/freshness verdict, NO `policy.yml` dial (FR-012); does NO I/O; emits
       NO CLI. The carried `RouteResult.Cost` is NOT evaluated.

       A pure leaf (`Ship -> {Enforcement, Route}`), reaching no git/filesystem/clock and needing no
       serialization ŌĆö so NO new third-party `PackageReference` (`System.*`/FSharp.Core only);
       `Gates`/`Findings`/`Config` flow transitively through `Route`. The whole surface is a pure total
       function ŌĆö no MVU ceremony (Principle IV). Compile order is Model.fsi -> Model.fs -> Ship.fsi ->
       Ship.fs: the result vocabulary, then the pure rollup. -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <RootNamespace>FS.GG.Governance.Ship</RootNamespace>
    <Version>0.1.0</Version>
    <!-- Optional library, but packable like Config/Routing/Gates/Route/RouteJson/GatesJson/Enforcement
         (overrides Directory.Build.props). -->
    <IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
    <PackageId>FS.GG.Governance.Ship</PackageId>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="Model.fsi" />
    <Compile Include="Model.fs" />
    <Compile Include="Ship.fsi" />
    <Compile Include="Ship.fs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.Enforcement/FS.GG.Governance.Enforcement.fsproj" />
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.Route/FS.GG.Governance.Route.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
